  <front>
   <head>SONG XXIV. The Child's Complaint.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">WHY should I love my Sports so well,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">So constant at my Play,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And lose the Thoughts of Heav'n and Hell;</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And then forget to pray?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">What do I read my Bible for,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">But, LORD, to learn thy Will;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And shall I daily know thee more,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And less obey thee still?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">How senseless is my Heart and wild!</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">How vain are all my Thoughts?</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Pity the Weakness of a Child,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And pardon all my Faults.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Make me thy heav'nly Voice to hear,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And let me love to pray;</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Since GOD will lend a gracious Ear</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">To what a Child can say.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
